section.def:
overburden (覆蓋層) means any
            other substance which overlies the granite, porphyry or limestone which is extracted in
            a quarry;

supervisor on duty (當值主管) means the approved supervisor or the approved deputy supervisor under
            whose supervision any work is for the time being carried on in a quarry in accordance
            with regulation 25(1) or (2);

Time Register (記時冊) means
            the register required to be kept and maintained in a quarry under regulation
                14(1)(c);

paragraph.content:
being the supervisor on duty in a quarry, permits any person to go or
                    remain on any top or face in the quarry in contravention of paragraph (1);
                    or

commits an offence under regulation 9, 14, 16,
                    20, 21, 22, 23, 24 or
                    57 is liable on conviction to a fine at level 4;

commits an offence under regulation 15, 17,
                    19(2)(a) or 25 is liable on conviction to a fine at level
                6;
